driftkit
========

Lightweight Parquet-first dataset stats and drift checker.

What it does
- Computes per-column stats from Parquet (row count, missing, distinct, numeric mean/std/min/max/histogram, categorical top values).
- Compares two Parquet snapshots to surface drift (missing-rate deltas, mean/std deltas, PSI for numeric, JSD for categorical).

Install (editable)
```
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
python3 -m pip install -e .
```

Quickstart (CLI)
- Stats: `driftkit stats path/to/file.parquet`
- Compare: `driftkit compare ref.parquet cur.parquet`
Both print JSON/text to stdout; redirect to a file if desired.

Python API
```python
import driftkit as dk

ref = dk.compute_stats("ref.parquet")
cur = dk.compute_stats("cur.parquet")
drift = dk.compare_datasets(ref, cur)
print(dk.format_drift_report(drift))
```

Project layout (v0.1)
- `driftkit/`: library and CLI entrypoint.
- `examples/`: example assets (generated Parquet files are ignored).
- `tests/`: smoke tests (currently ignored from VCS; keep locally for dev).

Limits (v0.1)
- Parquet-only ingest; other formats not yet supported.
- No schema validation; columns missing or type-mismatched are skipped in compare.
- PSI uses numpy histograms; JSD uses value counts (heavy on very high-cardinality columns).
